After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor of offensive basket interference is overturned. There is clear and conclusive evidence that Green (GSW) does not touch the ball and -- although Green makes contact with the rim -- contacting the rim, standing alone, does not violate the rule.  In order for contact with the rim to constitute offensive basket interference when the ball is not in the net, it must (a) occur while the ball is sitting or rolling on the rim and using the rim as its lower base, (b) cause the ball to take an unnatural bounce, or (c) move the rim off-center.  None of those conditions were satisfied on this play, so there was no basket interference.

James' (LAL) successful shot attempt was initially ruled a two-point shot by on-court referees.  Upon review by the NBA Replay Center Official, there was not clear and conclusive visual evidence that the on-court ruling was incorrect, and therefore no basis to overturn that ruling.  When James raises his heels to jump for his shot, the replay shows his right foot rolling forward so that the toe of his shoe contacts the three-point line.  For a player's shot to be scored a three-point field goal, the player may not touch the three-point line until after his shot is released.

On replay review, the coach's challenge of the shooting foul called on Hield (IND) was deemed successful.  The video clearly shows that Hield reaches forward and makes contact with the ball from behind Brown (BOS).  While in contact with the ball, Hield also makes minimal contact with Brown's head, and on review that contact was correctly deemed incidental.  As the rulebook makes clear, the mere fact that contact occurs does not necessarily constitute a foul; contact which is incidental to an effort by a player to defend an opponent, reach a loose ball, or perform normal defensive or offensive movements is not considered illegal.  Play resumed with IND possession, since Nesmith (IND) had imminent possession at the point of interruption.

Brunson (NYK) commits a take foul on Harris (PHI).
Batum (PHI) moves alongside Brunson's (NYK) path and marginal body contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Hart (PHI) commits a take foul on Maxey (PHI).
DiVincenzo (NYK) maintains a legal guarding position along Maxey's (PHI) path.
Oubre Jr. (PHI) and Brunson (NYK) momentarily engage and disengage off-ball, tangling momentarily before the interaction dissolves.
Batum's (PHI) right hand comes out slightly as Hart (NYK) launches into the air and marginal brush contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Embiid (PHI) raises his right arm up and marginal contact occurs with Hart's (NYK) wrist after he releases his put-back attempt at the basket.
Harris' (PHI) off-arm comes out slightly as he stops his forward momentum and marginal contact occurs with Hart's (NYK) side at the end of the drive.
Oubre Jr. (PHI) extends his arms and impedes Brunson's (NYK) FOM before Brunson grabs his arm.
Brunson (NYK) stops progressing and starts his shooting motion in front of Oubre Jr. (PHI), who continues into him from behind.
Embiid (PHI) firms up in DiVincenzo's (NYK) path and does not deliver any illegal contact when setting the pick.
Hartenstein (NYK) jumps from point A to point B into Maxey (PHI) and the body contact affects Maxey's driving shot attempt.

Hartenstein (NYK) touches the ball after it comes into contact with the backboard, while it is above rim-level with a chance to score. The call was confirmed by the Replay Center, the basket scored and Maxey awarded one free throw.
Oubre Jr. (PHI) grasps and promptly releases the side of Hart's (NYK) jersey as he moves to set the screen.
Oubre Jr.'s (NYK) left hand lightly brushes Brunson's (NYK) front as he cuts over the screen and the contact is marginal.
Oubre Jr. (PHI) comes alongside Brunson's (NYK) path and marginal contact occurs during the drive towards the sideline.
Oubre Jr. (PHI) turns slightly as he firms up over his left leg in Anunoby's (NYK) path and marginal contact occurs as the two players come together during the screen.
Anunoby (NYK) retreats alongside Embiid's (PHI) path and marginal body contact occurs during the post shot attempt.
Batum (PHI) rests his forearm on Brunson's (NYK) side and the contact prior to Brunson's pass is marginal.
Embiid (PHI) commits a take foul on DiVincenzo (NYK). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.

McBride (NYK) commits a take foul on Maxey (PHI). The take foul occurs prior to Maxey beginning an upward shooting motion. The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
Aunuoby (NYK) firms up over his left leg in Batum's (PHI) path and marginal contact occurs as they come together during the screen.
Batum (PHI) commits a take foul on Brunson (NYK). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
McBride (NYK) makes last contact with the ball prior to it falling out of bounds. Possession is properly awarded to Philadelphia.
McBride (NYK) makes marginal contact with Hield (PHI) as he receives the pass and before he starts his upward shooting motion.
McBride (NYK) pulls his hands away from Hield (PHI) and avoids making any illegal contact during his contest of Hield's perimeter jump shot attempt.
Middleton (MIL) establishes himself in Nembhard's (IND) path and absorbs the marginal contact during the screen.
Nembhard (IND) legally contests Lillard's (MIL) jump shot attempt.
Turner (IND) stops short behind Middleton (MIL) without delivering contact and the ensuing contact is marginal.
Middleton (MIL) and Turner (IND) briefly engage and disengage with one another pursuing the loose ball.
Middleton (MIL) is called for stepping on the sideline out of bounds and there is no clear and conclusive video evidence  that confirms that he avoids stepping out of bounds.
Portis (MIL) reaches in and makes clean contact with the ball to dislodge it from Turner (IND).  Any follow-through contact after the ball is dislodged by Portis's forearm is incidental.
Portis (MIL) is the last player to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds after dislodging it from Turner (IND).
Middleton (MIL) maintains a legal guarding position alongside Nesmith (IND) as incidental contact occurs during the drive and shot attempt.
Lopez (MIL) legally contests Nesmith's (IND) jump shot, making "high-five" contact after the ball is released.
Siakam (IND) and Portis (MIL) mutually engage and disengage during the rebound. Siakam remains in bounds while securing the rebound and passing the ball.
Beverley (MIL) briefly wraps an arm around Haliburton (IND) while engaging on the perimeter.  He then places his hands near Haliburton's sides without grabbing him or affecting his FOM.
Beverley (MIL) reaches across and initiates contact with Nembhard's (IND) arm during the drive, affecting Nembhard's SQBR.

Nesmith (IND) moves alongside of Lillard (MIL) on the perimeter and marginal contact occurs as the two players come together.  When contact occurs, Lillard quickly gathers and enters his shooting motion but there is no illegal contact during Lillard's shot attempt.
Lopez (MIL) briefly grasps Turner's (IND) arm before Turner sets the pick.
Turner (IND) firms up in Beverley's (MIL) path and absorbs the incidental contact as they come together during the pick.
Lopez (MIL) legally contests Haliburton's (IND) jump shot, making "high-five" contact after the ball is released.
Siakam (IND) rests his hands on Portis's (MIL) back during the rebound and releases away without dislodging Portis from his position.

Replay review of the foul called on Lillard (MIL) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful. Lillard is late to the spot and still moving laterally prior to illegal contact occurring with Siakam (IND) during the play at the basket.
Siakam (IND) is moving alongside Middleton's (MIL) path and marginal body contact occurs during the drive.
Nesmith (IND) contests the driving shot attempt and marginal body contact occurs with Middleton (MIL) after the release.
Lillard (MIL) and Nembhard (IND) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs off-ball.
Beverley (MIL) commits a take foul on Nesmith (IND).
Turner (IND) moves slightly forward and marginal body contact occurs with Middleton (MIL) as Middleton dribbles around Turner on the perimeter.
Nesmith (IND) contests the jump shot attempt and avoids making contact with Middleton (MIL).
Siakam (IND) and Middleton (MIL) mutually engage and disengage as marginal contact occurs off-ball before Siakam receives the inbound pass.
Middleton (MIL) contests the jump shot attempt and avoids making contact with Siakam's (IND) arm.
Lopez (MIL) contests Haliburton's (IND) jump shot and the contact after the release, and follow-through, is marginal.
Siakam (IND) extends his right arm out and initiates illegal contact with Lillard's (MIL) face during the rebound.
Siakam (IND) moves forwards into Portis (MIL), who briefly has a hold of Siakam's arm during the rebound.  The contact between the two players is marginal.
Turner (IND) extends his hands into Middleton (MIL) while he is airborne during the dunk attempt, affecting his trajectory.

Beverley (MIL) reaches across Nembhard's (IND) body and Nembhard briefly grasps Beverley's arm in response, causing him to lose control of his dribble.  Nembhard losing possession of the ball is not a result of any illegal contact from Beverley.
Nembhard (IND) loses control of the ball on his gather and Beverley's (MIL) foot makes contact with the loose ball as it rolls out of bounds.
Portis (MIL) legally contests Siakam's (IND) jump shot attempt.
Middleton (MIL) wraps his arm around Nembhard (IND), which impedes his ability to pursue the rebound.
Middleton (MIL) mutually engages with Nesmith (IND) off-ball and marginal contact occurs as Middleton releases away to retrieve the pass.
Siakam (IND) fails to fully clear the lane and is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Nesmith (IND) legally contests Middleton's (MIL) jump shot attempt.
Siakam (IND) and Portis (MIL) mutually engage and disengage as marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
Middleton (MIL) establishes himself in Nembhard's (IND) path and marginal contact occurs as they come together during the pick.

Lopez (MIL) establishes himself in Nembhard's (IND) path and does not deliver illegal contact.  He turns as Nembhard attempts to move over the screen and the two players engage, but he does not extend into his path.
Turner (IND) legally contests Middleton's (MIL) jump shot attempt.
Beverley (MIL) initiates illegal contact with Haliburton's (IND) head during his driving shot attempt.
Nesmith (IND) and Middleton (MIL) mutually engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs off-ball.
Nesmith (IND) legally contests Middleton's (MIL) jump shot attempt.
Banchero (ORL) brings his arm toward Strus' (CLE) path and marginal contact occurs during Strus' drive.
Carter Jr. (ORL) is actively guarding an opponent within three seconds of entering the lane.
Banchero (ORL) legally contests Mobley's (CLE) dunk attempt.
Mobley (CLE) legally contests Banchero's (ORL) jump shot attempt.
Suggs (ORL) moves into and initiates contact with Mitchell's (CLE) body, which affects Mitchell's SQBR on the perimeter.
Mitchell (CLE) briefly grasps Isaac's (ORL) jersey and marginal contact occurs as he immediately slides his hand off Isaac's side during the roll to the basket.
Mobley (CLE) initiates contact to Banchero's (ORL) right arm, affecting his SQBR during the driving shot attempt.
Suggs (ORL) avoids contact with Mobley's (CLE) arm on his dislodge attempt during the play at the basket.
Banchero (ORL) establishes himself in Strus' (CLE) path and does not deliver illegal contact during the pick.
Mobley (CLE) legally contests Wagner's (ORL) driving shot attempt.
Mobley (CLE) firms up in Suggs' (ORL) path and absorbs the contact that occurs as they come together during the screen.
Wagner (ORL) briefly places a hand to Mitchell's (CLE) front and Mitchell moves through the marginal contact on the perimeter.
Wagner (ORL) legally contests Mitchell's (CLE) jump shot attempt.
As he disengages from the pick, Banchero (ORL) brings his hands toward Strus (CLE) and marginal contact occurs as Banchero releases away to the perimeter.
Mobley (CLE) legally contests and cleanly blocks Wagner's (ORL) driving shot attempt.
Carter Jr. (ORL) and Morris Sr.'s (CLE) arms get briefly tangled during the rebound.
Wagner (ORL) commits a take foul on Mitchell (CLE).
Morris Sr. (CLE) briefly engages and immediately disengages with Banchero (ORL) as marginal contact occurs off-ball during the inbound.

Morris Sr. (CLE) firms up in a legal guarding position in front of Banchero (ORL).  As Banchero elevates for the jump shot attempt, Morris Sr. remains in his legally obtained position and does not step forwards and the incidental contact is a result of Banchero drifting forwards into Morris Sr.
Garland (CLE) is firming up on his right foot as he establishes himself in Suggs' (ORL) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Mobley (CLE) makes contact with Banchero's (ORL) left arm that causes him to lose control of the ball.
Mitchell (CLE) uses his off-arm to brace for the ensuing marginal contact with Carter Jr. (ORL) as he contests the driving shot attempt.
Suggs (ORL) briefly rests a hand on Mitchell's (CLE) back and marginal body contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Banchero (ORL) and Strus (CLE) mutually engage and when Banchero disengages, Strus loses his balance on his own.
Anthony (ORL) makes body contact with Okoro (CLE) that affects his return to the floor as they pursue the rebound.
Carter Jr. (ORL) is adjusting alongside Mitchell's (CLE) path during the drive and incidental foot to foot contact occurs before Mitchel releases the pass.
Isaac (ORL) and Garland (CLE) pursue the loose ball and incidental hand contact occurs before Isaac secures possession.
Mitchell (CLE) grabs Banchero's (ORL) off-arm as he attempts to dislodge the ball away.
Okoro (CLE) commits a take foul on Suggs (ORL).
Banchero (ORL) is retreating in Mitchell's (CLE) path and absorbs the marginal body contact that occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Mobley (CLE) commits a take foul on Carter Jr. (ORL).
Gilfeous-Alexander (OKC) reaches across Jones' (NOP) body and initiates contact that affects his SQBR as he is dribbling on the perimeter.
Nance Jr. (NOP) establishes himself in Dort's (OKC) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Ingram (NOP) delivers contact to Dort (OKC) that dislodges him from his defensive position in the post.
Jones (NOP) contests Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) jump shot and the contact after the release, and follow-through, is marginal.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) briefly holds Nance Jr.'s (NOP) left arm as the two players engage during the rebound.
Williams (OKC) legally contests Ingram's (NOP) jump shot attempt.

Ingram's (NOP) shot attempt makes contact with the rim and the shot clock does not reset.  The official blows play dead to address the clock malfunction and play resumes with NOP possession and 12 seconds remaining on the shot clock.
Holmgren (OKC) cleanly blocks the shot attempt prior to when the ball reaches its apex.
McCollum (NOP) lowers his arm and initiates illegal contact to Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) left arm during his driving shot attempt.
Murphy III (NOP) establishes himself in Williams's (OKC) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Wallace (OKC) legally contests McCollum's (NOP) jump shot attempt.
Murphy III (NOP) initiates illegal contact to Williams' (OKC) head as he steps through the double team on the perimeter.
McCollum (NOP) initiates contact with Holmgren's (OKC) arm and affects Holmgren's SQBR.
Valanciunas (NOP) establishes himself in Williams' (OKC) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Murphy III (NOP) establishes himself in Williams' (OKC) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Wallace (OKC) reaches in and marginal contact occurs with McCollum's (NOP) right arm as he briefly loses possession of the ball on his own.
Wallace (OKC) legally contests McCollum's (NOP) jump shot attempt.
Jokic (DEN) straddles the lane line and is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Jokic (DEN) is already in Reaves' (LAL) path and does not deliver contact during the pick.
James (LAL) has a resting hand on Jokic's (DEN) upper body and marginal contact occurs when he releases on the switch during the pick.
Jokic (DEN) establishes himself in Reaves' (LAL) path and absorbs the marginal contact as they come together during the pick.
James (LAL) makes clean contact with the ball and deflects away Murray's (DEN) pass attempt.
Murray (DEN) brushes James' (LAL) arm and leg as marginal contact occurs that James moves through to finish at the rim.
Russell (LAL) moves to Jokic's (DEN) side and avoids making contact with Jokic as he attempts to pass.
Reaves (LAL) and Gordon (DEN) make clean contact with the ball, and the ensuing contact as Gordon secures the ball is incidental.
Russell (LAL) legally contests Porter Jr.'s (DEN) jump shot attempt.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court (successful 3pt. field goal) was confirmed.
Murray (DEN) applies a resting forearm to Russell's (LAL) side, and marginal contact occurs as he removes it during Russell's driving shot attempt.
Jokic (DEN) is firming up over his right foot in James' (LAL) path, and the contact as the defenders switch is marginal.

James (LAL) extends his forearm out and initiates contact with Murray's (DEN) front, which affects his SQBR at the end of the drive. The illegal contact occurs prior to Murray's gather and a non-shooting foul is correctly assessed.
Russell (LAL) gives a step of distance when establishing himself in Gordon's (DEN) path, and he absorbs the contact to his upper body.
Caldwell-Pope (DEN) brushes James' (LAL) arm during the driving shot attempt, and the ensuing follow-through contact to James' lower body is marginal.
James (LAL) legally contests Murray's (DEN) jump shot attempt.

James stops his forward momentum to release away from the marginal contact while Caldwell-Pope (DEN) briefly grasps his arm before the shot attempt.  Additionally, Caldwell-Pope loses his balance on his own accord by contorting his body in an attempt to get over the pick.
Davis (LAL) legally contests Murray's (DEN) jump shot attempt.
Davis (LAL) absorbs the contact from Jokic (DEN) as they come together in the post.
Davis (LAL) legally contests Caldwell-Pope's (DEN) jump shot attempt.
Russell (LAL) applies his forearm to Jokic's (DEN) upper body, and the contact as Jokic secures the rebound is marginal.
James (LAL) goes to, not through, Gordon's (DEN) space and they briefly engage and disengage off ball.
Caldwell-Pope (DEN) brushes Reaves' (LAL) arm as he gathers the ball, and the contact is marginal.
Jokic (DEN) brings his forearm towards James' (LAL) upper body, and he removes his arm while absorbing the marginal contact from James.
Gordon (DEN) applies a resting forearm on James' (LAL) body, and marginal contact occurs as he moves alongside James' path during the driving shot attempt.
Murray (DEN) brings his off-arm toward Reaves (LAL) and marginal contact occurs as Murray releases away from Reaves.
Jokic (DEN) is already in Reaves' (LAL) path and he absorbs the contact during the pick.
Reaves (LAL) brushes Murray's (DEN) arm and the contact at the start of the drive is marginal.
Jokic (DEN) is firming up over his left leg in Reaves' (LAL) path and he absorbs the contact.
Davis (LAL) legally contests Murray's (DEN) jump shot attempt.
Gordon (DEN) cleanly deflects the ball away from James (LAL) as they engage for rebounding positioning.
James (LAL) brings his arm down as he pursues the rebound, and the contact with Gordon's (DEN) arm as he secures possession is marginal.
Hachimura (LAL) avoids making contact with Murray's (DEN) body during the jump shot attempt.
Davis (LAL) is firming up over his right leg in Murray's (DEN) path and he absorbs the contact during the pick.
Jokic (DEN) is moving alongside Reaves' (LAL) path and marginal body contact occurs as they come together during the drive.
Murray (DEN) and Davis (LAL) come together at the same spot off ball, and the contact is marginal.
Russell (LAL) brings his hand towards Jokic's (DEN) arm/wrist and marginal contact occurs as Jokic completes his desired pass.
Russell (LAL) brushes Jokic's (DEN) arm as he defends the pass, and the contact is marginal.
Jokic (DEN) applies his hand to Russell's (LAL) side and marginal contact occurs as he releases away to receive the pass.
James (LAL) stops his forward momentum as he and Jokic (DEN) come together in the lane, and marginal contact occurs as Jokic moves forward towards the basket.
Reaves (LAL) clamps and holds Gordon's (DEN) arm, which affects his ability to secure the rebound with both hands.
Gordon (DEN) is the last player to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds.  Possession is correctly awarded to the Lakers.
Porter Jr. (DEN) extends his arm forward and initiates contact with James' (LAL) shoulder that affects his driving shot attempt.
Davis (LAL) brings his forearm towards Jokic's (DEN) path, and marginal contact occurs as they briefly engage and disengage off ball.
Jokic (DEN) brings his hands toward Reaves (LAL), and the contact as Jokic releases away to roll is marginal.
Reaves (LAL) legally contests Murray's (DEN) jump shot attempt.
Jokic (DEN) is moving alongside James' (LAL) path, and marginal contact occurs as they come together at the same spot in the backcourt.
Caldwell-Pope (DEN) is in a legally obtained position when Prince's (LAL) momentum causes him to drift forward into Caldwell-Pope as he releases the jump shot attempt.
Jones Jr. (DAL) and George (LAC) engage and disengage with one another, and marginal contact occurs along the perimeter.
Jones Jr. (DAL) brushes George's (LAC) right side and arm, and marginal contact occurs as George passes at the end of the drive.
Kleber (DAL) initiates contact with Zubac's (LAC) left arm and causes him to lose control of the ball during his upward shooting motion.
Washington (DAL) avoids making arm contact with Leonard (LAC) and legally contests his jump shot attempt.
Harden (LAC) brings his left hand forward and marginal contact occurs with Doncic's (DAL) off-arm on the perimeter.
Harden (LAC) legally contests Doncic's (DAL) jump shot attempt.
Westbrook (LAC) initiates body contact with Doncic (DAL) and affects his SQBR in the backcourt.
Irving (DAL) and George (LAC) engage and disengage with one another prior to Irving releasing away for the inbound.
George (LAC) and Jones Jr. (DAL) engage and disengage with one another as the pick expires.
Harden (LAC) moves laterally and marginal body contact occurs with Irving (DAL) as he accelerates during the drive.
George (LAC) brings his left forearm toward Jones Jr.'s (DAL) back and marginal contact occurs as Jones Jr. elevates from underneath the basket in pursuit of the rebound.
Irving (DAL) cleanly dislodges the ball away from Leonard (LAC) after Leonard secures the rebound.
George (LAC) releases his off-arm away from Jones Jr.'s (DAL) front after they come together during the drive.
Jones Jr.'s (DAL) left leg is slightly extended outward toward George's (LAC) path and marginal body contact occurs as George drives toward the lane.
Jones Jr. (DAL) jumps to contest and marginal contact occurs with Zubac's (LAC) right arm that does not affect his dunk attempt.
George (LAC) initiates body and arm contact with Washington (DAL), affecting Washington's SQBR as he starts his dribble.

Jones Jr. (DAL) initiates illegal contact with George's (LAC) front and left arm. The contact occurs prior to the start of George's upward shooting motion and the play is correctly deemed a non-shooting foul.
Westbrook (LAC) extends both hands into Washington's (DAL) side and initiates contact that causes Washington to become dislodged after he releases the pass.
Leonard (LAC) commits a take foul on Jones Jr. (DAL).
Powell (LAC) brings his left arm forward as he establishes himself in Jones Jr.'s (DAL) path and he does not deliver illegal contact when he sets the screen during the inbound.
Harden (LAC) and Doncic (DAL) engage and disengage with one another, and marginal contact occurs during the inbound.

Replay review of the foul called on Irving (DAL) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed successful. Irving makes contact with the ball and the part of Leonard's (LAC) left hand that is on the ball, legally contesting the driving shot attempt.  The basket is scored and DAL receives possession of the ball when play resumes.
Mann (LAC) briefly places a hand on Washington's (DAL) back and the contact is marginal.
Harden (LAC) commits a take foul on Irving (DAL).
Mann (LAC) briefly has a grasp of Kleber's (DAL) right arm and then releases during the rebound.
Harden (LAC) commits a take foul on Irving (DAL).
Washington (DAL) stops short of George (LAC) to contest the jump shot attempt and marginal contact occurs with George's slightly extended right leg after the release.
Mann (LAC) moves alongside Irving's (DAL) path and legally contests Irving's driving shot attempt.
George (LAC) rests and removes his forearm from Kleber's (DAL) back and the contact during the rebounding opportunity is marginal.
Zubac (LAC) brings his arms out slightly and marginal contact occurs with Kleber (DAL) as he launches into the air during the rebounding opportunity.
Washington (DAL) rests and promptly removes his hand from Harden's (LAC) front during the drive.
Washington (DAL) swipes his hand down at the ball and makes contact with Harden's (LAC) left arm, which alters his driving shot attempt in the paint.
Coffey (LAC) and Washington (DAL) come together off-ball as Washington moves to set a pick and the contact is marginal.
Coffey (LAC) pulls Doncic's (DAL) right arm and delivers contact that affects Doncic's ability to gather the ball.
Washington's (DAL) forearm brushes Harden's (LAC) side as Washington attempts to align along Harden's path and the contact at the start of the drive is marginal.
Washington (DAL) rests and removes his marginal hand contact from Harden's (LAC) lower back during the driving shot attempt.
Kleber (DAL) is firming up in George's (LAC) path when marginal contact occurs as George moves into the pick.

Washington (DAL) is trailing George (LAC) as both players run towards the frontcourt and incidental foot to foot contact occurs, which results in Washington temporarily losing his balance and falling to the floor.
Jones Jr. (DAL) wraps his right arm around George's (LAC) waist and the contact affects George's SQBR with the ball.
Jones Jr. (DAL) turns slightly as he firms up in Westbrook's (LAC) path and marginal brush contact occurs as Westbrook defends around the screen.
Green (DAL) comes alongside Harden (LAC) and marginal contact occurs at the start of Harden's dribble.
Green (DAL) commits a take foul on Harden (LAC). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
After the inbounds pass is released into the air, Westbrook (LAC) clamps and holds Irving's (DAL) right arm, which affects his ability to get to the pass.
Jones Jr. (DAL) commits a take foul on George (LAC). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
Irving's (DAL) arms come out slightly as he releases away from Coffey (LAC) and the contact during the inbounds is marginal.
Mann (LAC) legally contests Doncic's (DAL) jump shot, making 'high-five' contact after the ball is released.
There is no clear and conclusive video evidence that shows Coffey (LAC) does not make last contact with the ball prior to it bouncing out of bounds. Possession is properly awarded to Dallas.

Replay review of the foul called on Haliburton (IND) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed successful. Haliburton cleanly deflects the ball away from Brunson (NYK), and the ensuing arm contact is incidental.  At the time of the whistle, the Pacers had imminent possession and play correctly resumes with Indiana ball.
Hartenstein (NYK) briefly grasps and releases Turner's (IND) arm.
DiVincenzo (NYK) makes clean contact with the ball as he defends Nembhard's (IND) drive.
DiVincenzo (NYK) maintains a legal guarding position on Nembhard's (IND) driving shot attempt.
Nembhard (IND) and DiVincenzo (NYK) engage and disengage on the pick.
Turner (IND) fails to fully clear and is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Nembhard (IND) firms up in Brunson's (NYK) path on his drive and maintains a legal guarding position.
Turner (IND) establishes a legal position on Hart's (NYK) side before the contact.
After establishing a legal screening position in Nesmith's (IND) path, DiVincenzo (NYK) clamps his arm and prevents him from disengaging.
Nesmith (IND) makes contact to the ball with his hand, not his foot. There is no replay trigger to review a kicked ball call.
Nembhard (IND) maintains a legal guarding position while defending Brunson (NYK).
DiVincenzo (NYK) is moving sideways along Siakam's (IND) path in a legal guarding position when Siakam steps on his foot.
Anunoby (NYK) maintains a legal guarding position, moving along Siakam's (IND) path on his drive.
Nembhard (IND) is in a legal position when Brunson (NYK) moves his arms from side-to-side with the ball, making contact with Nembhard's arm as he starts of his dribble.
Nembhard (IND) briefly grasps Brunson's (NYK) jersey during the inbound.

Replay review of the out of bounds call pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed successful. Nembhard (IND) is the last player to touch the ball before the ball goes out of bounds, and possession is correctly awarded to the Knicks. The game clock was re-set to 0:22.4.
Nembhard (IND) initiates contact with Brunson's (NYK) side while he is on the court without affecting his balance. Brunson then jumps to create space to throw the ball off Haliburton (IND).

call_type: Turnover:  Out of Bounds - Bad Pass Turn
comments: Brunson (NYK) jumps and throws the ball off of Haliburton (IND) before going out of bounds. The ball hits Haliburton while he is in the air, and therefore not yet out of bounds. The ball then bounces off of Haliburton and hits Brunson while he is out of bounds. Possession is correctly awarded to the Pacers.

Replay review of the foul called on Turner (IND) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful. Turner turns into DiVincenzo's (NYK) path and does not give him time and distance to change direction prior to the illegal contact.
Nembhard (IND) wraps Brunson's (NYK) side, affecting his FOM during the inbound.
Nembhard (IND) commits a take foul on Brunson (NYK).
Turner (IND) extends into DiVIncenzo's (NYK) path and delivers contact with his side during the screen.
Haliburton (IND) gathers the pass on his left foot and legally releases his dribble.
Hart (NYK) makes clean contact with the ball and deflects it away as Haliburton (IND) makes the pass.
Siakam (IND) grabs Hartenstein's (NYK) arms off-ball and the contact affects Hartenstein's ability to defend the oncoming driving shot attempt.
Haliburton (IND) moves laterally into Brunson's (NYK) path and initiates body contact that affects Brunson's SQBR during the drive.
Brunson (NYK) and Nesmith (IND) come together in pursuit of the loose ball and incidental leg-to-leg contact occurs.
Brunson (NYK) and Nesmith (IND) come together in pursuit of the loose ball and marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
Nesmith (IND) reaches in and marginal contact occurs with DiVincenzo's (NYK) arm.
